x4freetext: MAIN REF.
DATA ON DISKETTE.
-DOUBLE-DIFFERENTIAL NEUTRON EMISSION CROSS SECTION OF
BE-9.
THE 150 MEV GEEL LINAC, GELINA, GIVING NEUTRON
BURSTS OF 1 NS AT A RATE OF 800 HZ.
ROTARY URANIUM TARGET.
.WHITE NEUTRON SPECTRUM, WELL COLLIMATED.
THE INCIDENT NEUTRON ENERGIES WERE DETERMINED
WITH TIME-OF-FLIGHT TECHNIQUES.
PULSE-SHAPE DISCRIMINATION TECHNIQUES WERE USED
TO DISTINGUISH NEUTRONS FROM GAMMA RAYS.
THE ENERGIES OF THE SECONDARY NEUTRONS WERE
DETERMINED BY UNFOLDING THE RECORDED PULSE HEIGHTS
USING THE FORIST CODE AND THE DETECTOR RESPONSE
MATRIX.
THE EMITTED NEUTRONS WERE DETECTED WITH 8 NE213
LIQUID SCINTILLATORS, POSITIONED 20 CM FROM THE SAMPLE
AT DIFFERENT ANGLES.
A U-235 FISSION CHAMBER, PLACED IN THE NEUTRON
BEAM AT A DISTANCE OF 30 M FROM THE NEUTRON TARGET,
WAS USED TO MEASURE THE SHAPE OF THE INCIDENT NEUTRON
FLUX.
.A 0.0616 ATOMS/B THICK BE-9 SAMPLE, PSITIONED IN AN
EVACUATED TUBE AT ABOUT 60 M FROM THE NEUTRON SOURCE.
.THE SECONDARY NEUTRON ENERGY SPECTRA WERE CORRECTED
FOR SELF-SCREENING AND MULTIPLE SCATTERING IN THE
SAMPLE, AND FOR ATTENUATION OF THE EMITTED NEUTRONS
BY THE SAMPLE AND BY THE 1.5 MM THICK WALL OF THE AL
VACUUM TUBE. CORRECTIONS WERE ALSO APPLIED FOR BACK-
GROUND AND DEADTIME EFFECTS.
